01/IMG_1296-630x420.jpg 630w, https://sp-ao.shortpixel.ai/client/to_webp,q_glossy,ret_img,w_1260/https://tabloidmedia.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/IMG_1296-1260x840.jpg 1260w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" />Newcastle Mayor, Councillor Xolani Dube, is mourning the loss of his wife, Londiwe Dube, who passed away on Saturday, 15 January, after battling a long-term illness. The couple met in Melmoth where they had both worked at the time and were married for 17 years. Head of Communications of the Newcastle Municipality, Mlungisi Khumalo, said that they were deeply saddened by the passing of the Londiwe Dube. “The Newcastle Municipality, on behalf of all Newcastle residents, extends its heartfelt condolences to the first citizen of Newcastle, Mayor Xolani Dube, following the untimely passing of the town’s first lady, Mayoress Londiwe Dube. The municipality also wishes His Worship the Honourable Mayor Xolani Dube strength and courage during this difficult period,” said Khumalo. He further stated that that the community also mourns with the Dube family and will remember the late Mayoress as someone who was passionately and unequivocally supportive of any good cause.